This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with estimating scene flow in RGB-D videos. The paper also mentions potential applications in robotics, which suggests that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of deep learning methods for direct estimation of scene flow suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves estimation of motion vectors, which could also make it relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
